# QuickGrade AI Coding Rules

## Architecture
- Monorepo: pnpm workspaces + Turborepo
- Apps: apps/web (Next.js 15), apps/worker (QStash consumer)
- Packages: core, cache, db, observability, types, ui, config

## Security Rules
- NEVER log PII; use SHA-256 hashes for audit trails
- Always use Zod for input validation at API boundaries
- Wrap external API calls in CircuitBreaker from @markov/cache
- Use field-encrypt.ts for any student data before storage
- All mutations require idempotency-key header
- Audit logs are INSERT-ONLY; never UPDATE or DELETE

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode, no any types
- Use workspace:* for cross-package dependencies
- Prefer Edge runtime for stateless routes; Node for crypto/DB
- Return structured JSON format, never raw vendor responses
- Use crypto.randomUUID() for all UUID generation

## API Response Format
```json
{
  "data": { ... },
  "correlationId": "uuid",
  "timestamp": "ISO-8601"
}
```

Error format:
```json
{
  "error": { "code": "STRING", "message": "STRING" },
  "correlationId": "uuid",
  "timestamp": "ISO-8601"
}
```

## Database
- Use gen_random_uuid() for UUIDs (not uuid_generate_v4)
- Enable RLS on all tables
- audit_logs: INSERT-only, no UPDATE/DELETE policies
- submissions: index on image_hash for deduplication
- Auto-update updated_at via triggers

## Testing
- Unit tests: Vitest
- E2E tests: Playwright
- Run: pnpm test, pnpm test:e2e